events.title: Learn to Play: Pickleball
events.description: Have you heard about this crazy sport called Pickleball? It is a very easy to learn racquet sport and is catching on to be very popular amongst students. You can have the chance now at UTM to try this popular activity out for the first time! This June and/or July, join in on the 4-week UTM Beginner Pickleball Lessons being offered by skilled pickleball instructors at the UTM Tennis Courts. This is a great opportunity to learn the basics of the game in a beginner friendly environment. Players will be introduced to the proper technique for volleys, serves, forehand and backhand groundstrokes.  Don’t own a pickleball racquet? Don’t worry… we have you covered! Please Note: This program is for novice/new players only.

events.title: Learn to Play: Indoor Cricket
events.description: Ever wanted to learn the basic skills of Indoor Cricket or never had the chance to pick up this amazing sport? You have the chance now at UTM! This Winter, join in on the 4-week Learn to Play Indoor Cricket Lessons being offered by a skilled instructor in GYM A/B at the RAWC. This is a terrific opportunity to learn the basics of this sport in a beginner friendly environment. Players will be introduced to the proper technique for bowling, batting, defensive play and scoring!Please Note: This program is for novice/new players only.  Spots are limited so be sure to secure your spot!

Whether you have never played before or want to fine tune some of our skills, we welcome you to join so you can learn more from our Sport Instructors in a positive, engaging and fun environment.Please Note: This program is for novice/new players only.  Spots are limited so be sure to secure your spot!

announcements.title: Service Disruption: Parking Lots 4 and 8 Partial Closure
announcements.body:
Please be advised that Parking Lots 4 and 8, across the RAWC, will be partially closed starting **Wednesday, June 25 through August 2025** due to lot improvements and essential maintenance. This closure will affect both the lower and upper decks of P8 and P4.

Since parking will be limited at these areas, please plan your visit accordingly. For detailed information and alternative parking on campus, please refer to [this published notice by Facilities Management & Planning](https://www.utm.utoronto.ca/facilities/service-interruptions/notice-p4-p8-waterproofing-drainage-upgrade-starting-wednesday-june-25-2025 "https://www.utm.utoronto.ca/facilities/service-interruptions/notice-p4-p8-waterproofing-drainage-upgrade-starting-wednesday-june-25-2025").

We appreciate your understanding and patience during these closures.

announcements.title: Service Interruption: No Towel Service from July 21st to 25th
announcements.body: The campus will undergo an annual steam service maintenance period from **Monday, July 21 to Friday, July 25**. As a result, we will have to suspend towel service during this time. We appreciate your understanding.
